init

public init([any config='[runtime expression]'])
Constructor This creates a connection to a Couchbase server using the passed in config argument, which can be a struct literal of options, a path to a config object or an instance of a cfcouchbase.config.CouchbaseConfig object. For all the possible config settings, look at the CouchbaseConfig object.

Parameters:
config - The configuration structure, config object or path to a config object.

set

public any set(string key, any value, [numeric exp='0'], [numeric persistTo], [numeric replicateTo])
Set a value with durability options. This is a shorthand method so that you only need to provide a PersistTo value if you don't care if the value is already replicated. A PersistTo.TWO durability setting implies a replication to at least one node. This function returns a Java OperationFuture object (net.spy.memcached.internal.OperationFuture) or void (null) if a timeout exception occurs.

Parameters:
key - yes
value - yes
exp - The expiration of the document in minutes, by default it is 0, so it lives forever
persistTo - yes
replicateTo
